The paper addresses the problem of robot grasp optimization, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed algorithm uses Bayesian optimization, which is a popular machine learning technique (cs.AI). The algorithm also takes into consideration input noise, which is a common problem in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper includes simulations of robot grasping, which involves computer vision and image processing (cs.CV). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of reducing the risk of grasp failure, which is a safety issue (cs.SY).
